<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7ab509ab-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711"><num value="9711">§ 9711.</num><heading> Gap analysis on availability of snow-related data to assess and predict flood and flood impacts</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7ab509ac-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator, in consultation with the Department of Agriculture, the Department of the Interior, and the Army Corps of Engineers, shall conduct an analysis of gaps in the availability of snow-related data to assess and predict floods and flood impacts, including data on the following:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509ad-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> Snow water equivalent.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509ae-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> Snow depth.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509af-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> Snowpack temperature.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509b0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> Snow and mixed-phase precipitation.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509b1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> Snow melt.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509b2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/a/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> Rain-snow line.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7ab509b3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Report</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 180 days after <date date="2022-12-27">December 27, 2022</date>, the Administrator shall submit to the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate and the Committee on Science, Space, and Technology of the House of Representatives a report on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509b4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the findings of the gap analysis required by subsection (a); and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7ab509b5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s9711/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> opportunities for additional collaboration among Federal agencies to collect snow-related data to better assess and predict floods and flood impacts.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7ab509b6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/316/s16">Pub. L. 117–316, § 16</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4417">136 Stat. 4417</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
